OL,6,FMartin said Lodge, 58, from Goffstown,
OL,7,FNew Hampshire, treated the parts of
OL,8,F"beloved human beings as if they were
OL,9,Fbaubles to be sold for profit" and
OL,10,Fcollected thousands of dollars from
OL,11,F2018 to March 2020.
OL,13,FAfter Harvard finishes using a donated
OL,14,Fbody for research or teaching, the
OL,15,Fbody is typically returned to the
OL,16,Ffamily or cremated. Lodge acknowledged
OL,17,Fremoving body parts before cremation.
